		<!-- message -->
		<div>I use cd to keep aggro in most casses and was wondering what I should do if a failed mez happens and the adds go after the casters?  If I switch targets the one I'm on can't be mezzed because of the dot I put on them.  Should I just stick with the first mob that came in and let the others in the group worry about protecting the cleric or chanter or should I switch targets?  Chanters seem to wilt pretty fast in the mid 50's when they are being clobbered by 2 unslowed mobs that resisted the aoe mezz spell.<br />
<br />
Alot of times you get that cleric hotkey that they can't heal you if they are being hit message.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
