		<div>Taunting off chanters in groups is usually a bad idea; by the time you've done it he's usually either safe or dead already.  As you say they wilt quickly at high levels.<br />
<br />
For your second question: If a cleric yells for help after a failed mez I'd go for it and taunt the mob off him, but turn attack off and follow taunt with a terror immediately (terror works much better after a taunt) so the mob's safe to mez.  I have a hotbutton to say I'm doing this and it's safe to mez.<br />
<br />
This is because if the cleric's yelling for help it usually means he's decided there's not much chance the chanter will save him.<br />
<br />
It's a bit situational; a bad cleric will throw large heals on inc then spam the group for help in the 3 seconds it takes the chanter to mez the add off him, so you have to watch out for healers crying wolf too.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
