	<td class="alt1">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				<img class="inlineimg" src="images/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Default" border="0" />
				<strong>Good Chanters Shouldn't Need Help</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#000000" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>A good chanter shouldn't need help, other than heals to keep them alive.  I regularly partner up with an officer buddy and the 3 of us (65 SK/65 Shaman (me) and him 65 Chanter) go have fun.<br />
<br />
We went to Seb last week and decided to do Juggs, which was no problem.  The damn shrooms were a pain, though.  He had six mezzed at one time.  Thank god he regens mana like crazy, but has the UI with the timer, and knows his job well after 4 years.  Shaman kept him healed and the mezzed mobs slowed (refreshing occasionally), while  me and the pets just chewed on  mobs.  It was hella fun, actually.  <br />
<br />
He is an AC/HP Chanter, with no Ornate or Elem gear, but has close to 5k hp's fully buffed, plus his runes.  Good chanters are bitchen to watch.  They don't panic, they keep going for it.  All you need to do is keep them alive.  <br />
<br />
If people know their jobs, it's just a matter of keeping things going.  Don't switch.  Let the chanter mez, the healers heal, and the slowers slow.  You or someone decide which mobs to take next.  Take out the healing mobs first, and save the melee mobs for last.  <br />
<br />
The two of us rarely lfg anymore.  We just go around the game trying different encounters/zones where we once took several groups/raids a year or so ago.  Yeah, we wipe ocassionally, but we've got access to a clicker cleric when he's not also on, so it's no big deal.<br />
<br />
Once you get over the "death" thing, regardless of your class, this game becomes a lot more fun.  Shit, a couple of mobs in PoV or BoT, and we're back to where we were.  <br />
<br />
Let people do their jobs, and when you can, play with people that KNOW their class.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				Duke Oagan<br />
Dread Lord<br />
Tarrew Marr
			</div>
