		<!-- message -->
		<div>I've been grouping with a chanter for most of my career.  We started when she was lvl 6 and I was lvl 8.  Now both us 65.  In most cases you shouldn't have to worry about a chanter.  They do their job and you do yours.  It just depends on the situation.  Example:  In Ldon now if we don't have a bard single pulling, I'll just pull a room of three or so, one snared so it can't be mezzed.  I bring them back and she WoM the group.  I terror the one I've already called to the group as the kill target.  It then gets pulled out of the cluster.  While I hold aggro and the DPS finish it off she mezzes the rest.  Means I have to fight the first fight with an unslowed mob, but this is not a problem if I'm doing my job with lifetaps and the healer is watching.<br />
<br />
As said before the only time you have to grab one is if high resist or some DPS class gets trigger happy and wakes one up.  Then I just use fear to keep it off her till she gets it remezzed.  Have a lot of practice with that, cause she loves charming pets, and then hasting them.  That's the fun aggro game of keep the pet when it breaks mezz from killing the chanter.</div>
